-- Samudra Energy looks to raise up to $223 mln in Singapore IPO-term sheet
-- By Ngui Yantoultra and Saeed Azhar
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 08:58PM EDT
-- None



July 25 (Reuters) - Samudra Energy Ltd, is seeking to raise S$248 million to S$276.3 million ($223 million) in an initial public offering in Singapore, according to a term sheet seen by Reuters.

The company is selling about 131 million shares, excluding the greenshoe option, at an indicative price range of S$1.89 to S$2.11 a share, the term sheet said. Samudra Energy is part of private equity firm Northstar Group, which focuses on Indonesia and Southeast Asia.